comments.body:
[~spark],

Just curious, why do we need 'read'?  From a security best practice, isn't giving 'full_control' a bad idea (i.e. not least privilege)?  Am I missing something here [~rusvika]? With regards to 'DescribeServices', i thought euca-describe-services was deprecated? Right now, its a cloud admin tool.  If I run it and try to pass information from euca2ools configuration file, it barfs:
{code}
[root@c-02 ~]# euca-describe-services --region devops-admin@region-1
warning: euca-describe-services is deprecated; use ``empyrean-describe-services'' instead
__init__() got an unexpected keyword argument 'region'
{code}
If I run 'euca-describe-services' without creds, I get this:
{code}
[root@c-02 ~]# euca-describe-services
warning: euca-describe-services is deprecated; use ``empyrean-describe-services'' instead
{code}
